com.genebio.nextprot.dataloader.dto.RawA.description: Normal tissues showed weak to moderate cytoplasmic staining. Neuronal cells of hippocampus, exocrine pancreas, rectum and stomach displayed strong positivity. Subsets of cells in seminiferus ducts of testis exhibited strong cytoplasmic and nuclear staining. Fallopian tube exhibited moderate cytoplasmic and membranous positivity. Bile duct cells, cells in glomeruli, endocrine gland, Leydig cells, smooth muscle, cardiac myocytes, glial cells and mesenchymal cells were negative.
